WEBVTT

00:00:57.600 --> 00:01:03.536
and I looked at the first cover
drawn by Rea Irvin in 1925 --

00:01:03.560 --> 00:01:07.960
a dandy looking at a butterfly
through his monocle,

00:01:08.760 --> 00:01:11.520
and we call it Eustace Tilley.

00:01:12.080 --> 00:01:16.096
And I realized that
as the magazine had become known

00:01:16.120 --> 00:01:21.576
for its in-depth research
and long reports,

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:24.536
some of the humor
had gotten lost along the way,

00:01:24.560 --> 00:01:29.456
because now often Eustace Tilley
was seen as a haughty dandy,

00:01:29.480 --> 00:01:32.576
